<TITLE> Selim back to jail bidding his mother bye </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League presidium member Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim was taken back to jail Friday afternoon after he attended the last funeral prayers for his mother on parole, a jail official said. Deputy inspector general (prisons) Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com Selim was taken by a prison van at 3:30pm to Dhaka Central Jail from Banani graveyard after the burial of his mother. Achhia Khatun, mother of Selim and aunt of Awami League president Sheikh Hasina was buried Friday after she died Thursday of old-age complications aged 90. bdnews24.com senior correspondent Sumon Mahbub reported from Banani graveyard after the final prayers at the Gulshan central mosque she was buried at Banani graveyard beside the grave of her husband Sheikh Nurul Haq at 2:30pm. Selim was freed on parole for two hours 40 minutes Thursday night to have a last glimpse of his mother. Later he was released for five hours on parole to attend the final prayers for his deceased mother and her burial on Friday. The body was taken to Gulshan central mosque from her Banani residence at about 12:45pm. When the body was lifted to the truck the family members including Hasina and Selim burst into tears. Taken to the mosque in a prison van under special police guard, Selim said his Juma and funeral prayers. He was then driven to the graveyard and seated in the office room. After 15 minutes when the body arrived there, he held one side of the coffin with plainclothes and uniformed police all around him. He threw earth into the grave with three policemen behind him. His son Sheikh Fazle Fahim Subhash and elder brother Sheikh Fazlul Haq Moni's son barrister Sheikh Fazle Noor Tapash lowered their grandmother's body into the grave. Awami League presidium members Abdur Razzak, Tofail Ahmed, former speaker advocate Abdul Hamid, Bangladesh Jatiya Party chairman Naziur Rahman Monjur, Gano Forum leader Mostafa Mohsin Montu, Awami League leaders advocate Rahmat Ali, Abdul Matin Khasru, Jatiya Party leader Sheikh Shahidul Islam were present during the burial. At 9:54am, a prison with Selim on board left Dhaka Central Jail and reached Banani at 9:15am. The police sealed off Banani Road no 2/A where his home is. None other than close relatives and senior political leaders were allowed in the home. Hasina reached there at 9.30am. Workers Party president Rashed Khan Menon, Awami League leaders Matia Chowdhury, Mukul Bose, Mostafa Jalal Mohiuddin and Dipu Moni went there to console Selim. bdnews24.
